<TITLE> Easing of emergency won't affect security: Matin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)  Home adviser MA Matin has said he believes the relaxation of the state of emergency would not affect security. "I am sure there will be no disruption of law and order even though the state of emergency has been relaxed," adviser Matin told reporters on Monday at the Secretariat. On whether emergency would be further relaxed or lifted altogether now that the schedule for general and Upazila elections have been declared, he said: "The government is working on the issue. You will know everything in time." Chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda on Sunday said the general election would be held on Dec. 18, as announced earlier, but Upazila polls would take place in one go on Dec. 28. Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman said on Sunday that restrictions on the political parties would go immediately after the schedule was announced. bdne
